HEADWORD: Chazy epoch
<hw>Cha*zy" ep"och</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Geol.)</fld> <def>An epoch
at the close of the Canadian period of the American Lower Silurian
system; -- so named from a township in Clinton Co., New York. See the
Diagram under <er>Geology</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cheap</ent>⟦br⟧
